#Intro to AJAX

AJAX stands for Asynchronous JavaScript and XML.

AJAX let you update HTML without loading a new webpage
- only part of your page are being updated.

Webpages - ask info from web server.
Web server returns data to the web browser
Javascript processes that data to selectively change part of the web page.

Request - process of asking a server for information
Response - server sends back its answer

Clients - browsers

To see all AJAX request happening - open javascript console, right click or control click and choose LOG XML HTTP Requests.
